subs.text:
@bessbell Years ago, August heat wave, 1 or 2 am, no air conditioning, windows open, baby screaming in the apartment across the narrow alley.  These voices in the night:

Exhausted mother: “What does he want?!”

Bitter man, in a drawl: “He don’t wont sheeit.”

